==English==
===Etymology===
Coalitus Latin, mix together. Used by U.S. President George Bush in the beginning of the 21st century to identify a unique group of nations who joined the United States in the invasion of Iraq.

===Noun===
#  A temporary group, or union of organizations, usually formed for a particular advantage.
#  Any of a small group of nations offering soldiers to the United States in support of an invasion of Iraq because of negotiated compensation rather than an alliance when established allies declared the invasion was illegal.

